3. Yet notwithstanding of this, it is true, that an outward Repentance;
where there is no inward, real & sanctified change wrought, may hold off
for a time, or prorogue the inflicting of temporal strokes; as we see in Aabh,
Nineveth & others.



10. Paul did not meane such works only, when he excluded his own Righteousness.
Phil. 3: 9. Nor can such works be called works of Righteousness;
which yet are expresly excluded in this matter. Tit. 3: 5.
